===Etymology===
Late {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|frm}} {{term|vocatif|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|vocativus||calling|lang=la}}, from {{term|vocatus||invocation|lang=la}}, from {{term|vocare||to call|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|wek-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|wekʷ-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|wokʷ-||give vocal utterance, speak|lang=ine-pro}}. See Latin {{term|vox|vōx|lang=la}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or pertaining to calling; used in calling or [[vocation]].
# {{grammar}} used in address; [[appellative]]; — said of that case or form of the noun, pronoun, or adjective, in which a person or thing is addressed; as, ''Domine'', O Lord.

